        "timestamp": "2018-07-20 21:52:26.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> i would like to know if constants.java is already getting covered\n > through another class in code coverage?\n\nit should be, but whether it is or not is kind of irrelevant.  What's the point of testing that a constant value equals the constant value (i.e., itself)?  That just means that the test code has to be updated any time someone updates the constants - it just doesn't seem to add any value.",
