        "timestamp": "2018-07-23 20:38:43.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> > i would like to know if constants.java is already getting covered\n > > through another class in code coverage?\n > \n > it should be, but whether it is or not is kind of irrelevant. \n > What's the point of testing that a constant value equals the\n > constant value (i.e., itself)?  That just means that the test code\n > has to be updated any time someone updates the constants - it just\n > doesn't seem to add any value.\n\nIn fact, based on a quick test, it has no impact on code coverage, as JaCoCo doesn't report coverage statics on data fields.  As a result, this change should be abandoned.",
